  "title": "Chiller Technician",
  "description": "<p><u><em>Job details</em></u></p>\n<p>· $2000 - $3000 (Negotiable)</p>\n<p>· 5 days, 8.30am to 5.30pm</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><em>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</em></u></p>\n<p>· Installing, Trouble-shooting and maintaining Equipment Chiller systems at customers’ worksites</p>\n<p>· Repair and maintenance of chiller systems in a workshop e.g. leak repair, brazing, replacements of the compressor, condenser, evaporators etc.</p>\n<p>· Complying with service standards, work instructions and customers' requirements.</p>\n<p>· Assisting with customers' queries.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><em>Job Requirements</em></u></p>\n<p>· Nitec/Higher Nitec in any Engineering/Electronics discipline</p>\n<p>· Diploma in any Engineering/Electronics discipline</p>\n<p>· Training will be provided</p>\n<p>· Experience in Air-con repair and maintenance or in HVAC industries is a plus, but not necessary</p>\n<p>· Background in Refrigeration/Mechanical/Electrical Engineering is a plus, but not necessary</p>\n<p>· Understanding of principles of air conditioning, refrigeration and heating is a plus, but not necessary</p>\n<p>· Ability to work after hours, over weekends and on public holidays with short or no notice.</p>\n<p>· Candidate with Class 3 license will be a bonus</p>",
